---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Resizing - Worker Image CDN">
	<h1>Resizing</h1>
	<p>Resize images on the fly using the <code>w</code> and <code>h</code> query parameters. Aspect ratio is always preserved and images are never upscaled.</p>

	<div class="resize-demo">
		<div class="resize-demo-stage">
			<img
				id="resize-demo-img"
				src="https://demo-cloudflare-cdn.ciannavei.dev/images/examples/jojo-dio.jpg?w=720&quality=80"
				alt="Interactive resize demo"
				width="720"
			/>
		</div>
		<input type="range" id="resize-demo-slider" min="280" max="720" value="720" step="1" />
		<div class="resize-demo-readout">
			<span>Requested: <code id="resize-demo-requested">720</code>px</span>
			<span class="arrow">&rarr;</span>
			<span>Served: <code id="resize-demo-served">720</code>px</span>
		</div>
		<p class="resize-demo-note">The served value is snapped up to the nearest <a href="/steps">size step</a>.</p>
		<div class="resize-demo-url">
			<code id="resize-demo-url">/images/examples/jojo-dio.jpg?w=720</code>
		</div>
	</div>

	<h2>Parameters</h2>
	<table>
		<thead>
			<tr>
				<th>Parameter</th>
				<th>Description</th>
				<th>Example</th>
			</tr>
		</thead>
		<tbody>
			<tr>
				<td><code>w</code></td>
				<td>Target width in pixels</td>
				<td><code>?w=800</code></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td><code>h</code></td>
				<td>Target height in pixels</td>
				<td><code>?h=600</code></td>
			</tr>
		</tbody>
	</table>

	<h2>Behavior</h2>
	<table>
		<thead>
			<tr>
				<th>Parameters Provided</th>
				<th>Result</th>
			</tr>
		</thead>
		<tbody>
			<tr>
				<td><strong>Width only</strong> (<code>?w=800</code>)</td>
				<td>Height is calculated to preserve aspect ratio</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td><strong>Height only</strong> (<code>?h=600</code>)</td>
				<td>Width is calculated to preserve aspect ratio</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td><strong>Both</strong> (<code>?w=800&amp;h=600</code>)</td>
				<td>Uses whichever dimension results in the larger output (contain behavior)</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td><strong>No params</strong></td>
				<td>The image is served at its original dimensions</td>
			</tr>
		</tbody>
	</table>

	<h2>No upscaling</h2>
	<p>If the requested size is larger than the original image, the original dimensions are kept. The worker never upscales an image.</p>

	<h2>Supported input formats</h2>
	<p>Dimensions are read directly from the binary headers of the original image. The following formats are supported:</p>
	<table>
		<thead>
			<tr>
				<th>Format</th>
				<th>Metadata Read</th>
			</tr>
		</thead>
		<tbody>
			<tr>
				<td><strong>PNG</strong></td>
				<td>Dimensions from the IHDR chunk</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td><strong>JPEG</strong></td>
				<td>Dimensions from the SOF marker</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td><strong>WebP</strong></td>
				<td>Dimensions from VP8/VP8L frames</td>
			</tr>
		</tbody>
	</table>
	<p>If the format is unrecognized, the image is served without resizing.</p>

	<h2>Step snapping</h2>
	<p>Requested dimensions are snapped to the nearest <a href="/steps">size step</a> before processing. For example, <code>?w=500</code> snaps to <code>w=720</code> with the default step configuration.</p>

	<h2>Examples</h2>
	<pre><code>/photo.jpg?w=400
/photo.jpg?h=300
/photo.jpg?w=800&h=600</code></pre>
</Layout>

<script>
	const STEPS = [320, 480, 720];
	const IMAGE_PATH = "/images/examples/jojo-dio.jpg";
	const IMAGE_BASE = `https://demo-cloudflare-cdn.ciannavei.dev${IMAGE_PATH}`;

	const slider = document.getElementById("resize-demo-slider") as HTMLInputElement;
	const img = document.getElementById("resize-demo-img") as HTMLImageElement;
	const requestedEl = document.getElementById("resize-demo-requested")!;
	const servedEl = document.getElementById("resize-demo-served")!;
	const urlEl = document.getElementById("resize-demo-url")!;

	function snap(value: number): number {
		for (const step of STEPS) if (value <= step) return step;
		return STEPS[STEPS.length - 1];
	}

	let lastServed = 720;
	slider.addEventListener("input", () => {
		const requested = Number(slider.value);
		const served = snap(requested);
		requestedEl.textContent = String(requested);
		servedEl.textContent = String(served);
		urlEl.textContent = `${IMAGE_PATH}?w=${served}`;
		if (served !== lastServed) {
			img.src = `${IMAGE_BASE}?w=${served}&quality=80`;
			img.width = served;
			lastServed = served;
		}
	});
</script>

<style lang="scss">
	@use "../style/vars" as *;

	.resize-demo {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 12px;
		margin-bottom: $siteSpacing;

		&-stage {
			min-height: 200px;
			display: flex;
			align-items: flex-start;
			justify-content: flex-start;

			img {
				max-width: 100%;
				height: auto;
				border-radius: 8px;
				border: 1px solid $borderCol;
				transition: width 0.1s ease-out;
			}
		}

		input[type="range"] {
			width: 100%;
			height: 24px;
			background: transparent;
			appearance: none;
			-webkit-appearance: none;
			cursor: pointer;

			&::-webkit-slider-runnable-track {
				height: 6px;
				border-radius: 3px;
				background: $bgCard;
				border: 1px solid $borderCol;
			}

			&::-moz-range-track {
				height: 6px;
				border-radius: 3px;
				background: $bgCard;
				border: 1px solid $borderCol;
			}

			&::-webkit-slider-thumb {
				appearance: none;
				-webkit-appearance: none;
				width: 18px;
				height: 18px;
				border-radius: 50%;
				background: $mainCol;
				border: 2px solid $bgDark;
				margin-top: -7px;
				box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px $mainCol;
				transition: transform 0.1s ease-out, background 0.1s ease-out;
			}

			&::-moz-range-thumb {
				width: 18px;
				height: 18px;
				border-radius: 50%;
				background: $mainCol;
				border: 2px solid $bgDark;
				box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px $mainCol;
				transition: transform 0.1s ease-out, background 0.1s ease-out;
			}

			&:hover::-webkit-slider-thumb,
			&:focus::-webkit-slider-thumb {
				background: $mainColLight;
				transform: scale(1.1);
			}

			&:hover::-moz-range-thumb,
			&:focus::-moz-range-thumb {
				background: $mainColLight;
				transform: scale(1.1);
			}

			&:focus {
				outline: none;
			}
		}

		&-readout {
			display: flex;
			gap: 8px;
			align-items: center;
			font-size: 0.85rem;
			color: $textSecondary;

			.arrow {
				color: $mainCol;
			}

			code {
				color: $textPrimary;
			}
		}

		&-note {
			margin: 0;
			font-size: 0.75rem;
			color: $textSecondary;
			font-style: italic;
		}

		&-url {
			font-size: 0.85rem;

			code {
				color: $mainCol;
			}
		}
	}
</style>
